WEBVTT

00:01.202 --> 00:02.801
             [♪♪♪]

00:04.304 --> 00:05.403
            Jeannie.

00:07.674 --> 00:09.507
       [CLEARS THROAT]

00:09.509 --> 00:10.842
Uh, Jeannie.

00:10.844 --> 00:12.077
              Oh.

00:18.952 --> 00:20.753
Good morning,
master, darling.

00:20.755 --> 00:21.920
           Oh. Morning, Jeannie.

00:21.922 --> 00:23.355
Are you ready
for breakfast?

00:23.357 --> 00:25.457
      No, I'm gonna have to skip
        breakfast this morning.

00:25.459 --> 00:26.892
           I'm giving a lecture.

00:26.894 --> 00:29.194
Oh. The kind
you always give me?

00:29.196 --> 00:30.729
                   [CHUCKLES]
                    No. No.

00:30.731 --> 00:32.296
             This is on military
                  strategy.

00:32.299 --> 00:34.199
Oh, that sounds
exciting. Ha.

00:34.201 --> 00:36.268
Uh-- Uh, what does
it mean?

00:36.270 --> 00:37.736
                Militar-- Oh.
                Oh, it's, um--

00:37.738 --> 00:39.337
                  Well, we study
                 ancient battles

00:39.339 --> 00:40.706
                 and, uh, how
              they were planned,

00:40.708 --> 00:42.674
          and the mistakes that
        were made, and so forth.

00:42.676 --> 00:44.510
Oh, what are you
going to talk about?

00:44.512 --> 00:47.846
     I'll be talking about the
   Napoleonic Wars and Waterloo,

00:47.848 --> 00:50.115
and the, uh,
Russian invasion.

00:50.117 --> 00:51.416
                 Oh, I've never
                 heard of them.

00:51.418 --> 00:53.484
      You mean, you're not
     interested in history?

00:53.486 --> 00:56.522
 Oh, history is so dull, master.

00:56.524 --> 00:57.823
          Dull?

00:57.825 --> 01:01.292
The Napoleonic Wars?
Uh-- Uh, Marat?

01:01.294 --> 01:02.961
     Uh, Mme. Pompadour?
             Uh--

01:02.963 --> 01:05.296
        Marie Antoinette
saying to the starving peasants,

01:05.298 --> 01:06.998
      "Let them eat cake,"
      you call that dull?

01:07.000 --> 01:09.334
        Did she say that
      at Waterloo, master?

01:10.271 --> 01:12.271
      No. No. No, Jeannie.

01:12.273 --> 01:15.273
  Uh, at Waterloo, Wellington
  defeated Napoleon Bonaparte.

01:15.275 --> 01:17.008
                 Oh, I have
             heard of Napoleon.

01:17.010 --> 01:19.010
Oh, really.
I should hope so.

01:19.012 --> 01:22.013
As a matter of fact, there's
a picture in here somewhere.

01:22.015 --> 01:24.116
Oh, yeah-- The-- Here--
There's a picture of him.

01:24.118 --> 01:26.885
        JEANNIE:
Why does he have his hand
in his jacket, master?

01:26.887 --> 01:28.787
    Well, I don't know why--

01:28.789 --> 01:29.888
            [SCOFFS]

01:29.890 --> 01:31.756
       Anyhow, he was one
    of the greatest generals

01:31.758 --> 01:32.991
       that ever lived.

01:32.993 --> 01:35.560
  He saved France and started
       to bring democracy

01:35.562 --> 01:36.561
       to all of Europe.

01:36.563 --> 01:38.029
     And then what happened?

01:38.031 --> 01:39.631
         Well, he was--

01:39.633 --> 01:41.032
     He was badly advised.

01:41.034 --> 01:43.769
He trusted a general
named Pichegru.

01:43.771 --> 01:46.605
         And this Pichegru later
         tried to kill Napoleon.

01:46.607 --> 01:48.607
          I think that it was he
         that persuaded Napoleon

01:48.609 --> 01:50.709
           that he could conquer
              the whole world.

01:50.711 --> 01:53.812
         I wish I could have
    just one hour with Napoleon.

01:53.814 --> 01:55.280
             Well, I'll see you.

01:56.917 --> 01:58.316
          [CHATTERING]

02:02.489 --> 02:04.156
[PEOPLE LAUGHING]

02:06.527 --> 02:08.226
               Jeannie, what--
             What are you doing?

02:08.228 --> 02:10.360
Look at all the lovely
dresses, master.

02:10.363 --> 02:12.397
                  Yes, yes--
                     Say--

02:12.399 --> 02:14.399
           There's Napoleon.
      That's Napoleon Bonaparte.

02:14.401 --> 02:15.634
Oh, yes, of course.

02:15.636 --> 02:17.936
You said you wished to spend
an hour with him, master.

02:17.938 --> 02:19.638
   Go talk.
                 I didn't know
              I could do it now.

02:19.640 --> 02:21.907
Oh, you have no medals.
             Huh, I don't need--

02:21.909 --> 02:23.174
                Need any medals.

02:23.176 --> 02:24.676
  Ah.
                     Oh.

02:24.678 --> 02:25.777
 [GIGGLES]

02:25.779 --> 02:26.912
                 Oh. Thank you.

02:26.914 --> 02:28.447
Oh. Lovely.
                     Huh?

02:28.449 --> 02:30.682
       Jeannie, Jeannie...
 this is going a little too far.

02:30.684 --> 02:32.517
              Just leave me one.
Oh, no, master.

02:32.519 --> 02:33.618
             No, I mean it. One.

02:33.620 --> 02:35.153
[CLICKS TONGUE, WHINES]

02:37.524 --> 02:38.757
    [GIGGLES]
                     Oh, boy.

02:38.759 --> 02:40.525
             Thank you, Jeannie.

02:40.527 --> 02:42.894
    Do you know, this is the
greatest thing you've ever done?

02:42.896 --> 02:44.863
      Oh.
            I can change
    the whole course of history.

02:44.865 --> 02:46.331
Well, enjoy yourself, master.

02:46.333 --> 02:48.199
I-- I will go around
and explore the palace,

02:48.201 --> 02:49.501
and look at the dresses.

02:49.503 --> 02:50.669
       [GIGGLES]

02:50.671 --> 02:52.737
Oh, master, there's
a lovely one. Bye-bye.

02:52.739 --> 02:53.738
                    Bye.

02:53.740 --> 02:55.507
        [CLEARS THROAT]

02:57.777 --> 03:00.111
Uh, pardon me.
I-I don't mean to intrude.

03:00.113 --> 03:01.947
Uh, my name is
Major Anthony Nelson.

03:01.949 --> 03:03.982
You don't know me,
but I certainly know you.

03:03.984 --> 03:05.417
 You're "the Little Corporal."

03:06.620 --> 03:07.619
                    Execute him.

03:13.794 --> 03:16.561
             [♪♪♪]

04:02.342 --> 04:03.975
             [♪♪♪]

04:08.782 --> 04:10.048
W-wait, wait.
Now, please.

04:10.050 --> 04:11.483
I-- Take it easy.

04:11.485 --> 04:13.818
I, uh-- I don't
mean to offend you, sir.

04:13.820 --> 04:15.720
Everybody calls you
"the Little Corporal."

04:15.722 --> 04:17.622
 Those who do
  regret it.

04:17.624 --> 04:19.324
   I have some very valuable
          information.

04:19.326 --> 04:21.059
      As a matter of fact,
       the fate of Europe

04:21.060 --> 04:22.560
         may depend on
     your listening to me.

04:22.562 --> 04:24.029
         The fate of Europe?

04:24.031 --> 04:25.030
         Who sent you to me?

04:25.032 --> 04:26.364
   Uh, well, no one sent me.

04:26.366 --> 04:27.666
  I-I-- I came with a friend.

04:27.668 --> 04:28.867
          Well...
        [CLEARS THROAT]

04:28.869 --> 04:30.769
    ...as a matter of fact,
     I was about to deliver

04:30.771 --> 04:32.036
 a lecture on you this morning.

04:32.038 --> 04:33.371
              A lecture?

04:33.373 --> 04:35.507
What is this?
Pichegru, get rid of him.

04:35.509 --> 04:36.641
                  At once, sire.

04:36.643 --> 04:38.343
Pichegru. P--

04:38.345 --> 04:40.811
I wouldn't do that
if I were you, Mr. Napoleon.

04:40.813 --> 04:42.580
I-- This man is about to
assassinate you.

04:42.582 --> 04:43.882
General Pichegru?

04:43.884 --> 04:44.983
     [CHUCKLES]

04:46.120 --> 04:47.185
                   Take him
                  out of here!

04:47.187 --> 04:48.920
Hold on a minute.
            Wait, wait, wait!

04:48.922 --> 04:51.522
         This man amuses me.
   I want to speak to him alone.

04:51.524 --> 04:53.625
Nappy.
                Ah, my dear.

04:53.627 --> 04:55.060
I don't believe
we've met.

04:55.062 --> 04:57.328
             Uh, Major, uh--
         Oh, N-Nelson.

04:57.330 --> 04:59.230
        Major Anthony
           Nelson.

04:59.232 --> 05:01.032
 You're the Empress Josephine,
          aren't you?

05:01.034 --> 05:03.635
  Oh. oh, I love that
    speech you made

05:03.637 --> 05:05.036
  about, "Let them
     eat cake."

05:05.038 --> 05:06.705
    Oh, that was
  very kind of you.

05:06.707 --> 05:08.139
            That was
        Marie Antoinette.

05:08.141 --> 05:10.108
     Oh. Well, I--
      I'm sorry.

05:10.110 --> 05:11.509
I was never very good
     at history.

05:11.511 --> 05:12.877
      [ALL CHUCKLE]

05:12.879 --> 05:14.345
              Come, major.

05:14.347 --> 05:16.214
            Tell me some more
         of those funny stories.

05:16.216 --> 05:17.315
          [CHUCKLES]
           Oh, yes.

05:18.284 --> 05:19.918
           Is he not
           wonderful?

05:19.920 --> 05:21.252
             Who is he?

05:21.254 --> 05:24.623
    Oh, Major Nelson is a--
An expert on military strategy.

05:24.625 --> 05:25.623
                  He is?

05:25.625 --> 05:26.891
            Oh, yes.

05:26.893 --> 05:29.194
  He has some wonderful advice
    for Napoleon Bonaparte.

05:31.298 --> 05:32.530
             About <i> what?</i>

05:34.634 --> 05:35.633
           Oh, it...

05:35.635 --> 05:37.869
      has something to do
           with war.

05:37.871 --> 05:38.870
                 War?

05:42.443 --> 05:43.575
              Hm.

05:43.577 --> 05:45.877
     Well, Major Nelson,
     who sent you to me?

05:45.879 --> 05:47.712
Oh, no one
sent me to you, sir.

05:47.714 --> 05:50.648
You see, I-- I lecture on
military strategy at a--

05:50.650 --> 05:52.750
Uh, well-- Never mind.
It-- It--

05:52.752 --> 05:54.452
              Where did you hear
                  this rumor

05:54.454 --> 05:56.287
                   about General
                     Pichegru?

05:56.289 --> 05:57.355
I-It's not
a rumor, sir.

05:57.357 --> 05:58.356
         It's history.

05:58.358 --> 06:00.158
                History?
         Yes, yes.

06:00.160 --> 06:01.559
    Or at least it will be.

06:01.561 --> 06:03.861
            What I mean is
       you don't have to worry.

06:03.863 --> 06:05.030
        He's gonna try
         to kill you,

06:05.032 --> 06:06.631
        but you're gonna
      have him strangled.

06:06.633 --> 06:07.632
           Strangled?

06:07.634 --> 06:08.833
           [CHUCKLES]
         You amuse me.

06:08.835 --> 06:10.668
  Well, thank you very much.

06:10.670 --> 06:12.937
 I can't tell you what a thrill
    it is to meet you, sir.

06:12.939 --> 06:14.672
I mean, well,
it's--

06:14.674 --> 06:17.241
      You don't meet
   someone every day who--

06:17.243 --> 06:20.144
    Who devised a legal code
that's used all over the world.

06:20.146 --> 06:21.412
          A legal what?

06:21.414 --> 06:22.880
       The Code Napoleon.

06:22.882 --> 06:25.583
    Your code for abolishing
   imprisoning men for debt,

06:25.585 --> 06:27.452
um, ending
slavery,

06:27.454 --> 06:30.088
      protecting women's
      claims on property.

06:30.090 --> 06:31.690
   Those are excellent ideas.

06:31.692 --> 06:33.291
   You thought of them, sir.

06:33.293 --> 06:34.326
   Or at least you will.

06:34.328 --> 06:35.627
                     You're
                a fortuneteller?

06:35.629 --> 06:38.096
Oh. No, no, no, no. I'm a--
                Or a spy?

06:38.098 --> 06:40.331
Yeah, a fortuneteller.
Yes, that's right.

06:40.333 --> 06:41.532
               Well, major...

06:41.534 --> 06:43.235
                tell me about
                 the future.

06:43.237 --> 06:44.669
All right, sir.

06:44.671 --> 06:47.973
I can, uh, tell you just about
anything you'd want to know.

06:47.975 --> 06:49.707
Uh, what year
is this?

06:49.709 --> 06:50.809
         You're a fortuneteller,

06:50.811 --> 06:52.276
              and you don't know
               what year it is?

06:52.278 --> 06:54.278
 Well, um--

06:58.618 --> 07:01.085
        Uh-- It's 1803.

07:09.963 --> 07:11.696
         Get rid of it.

07:12.799 --> 07:14.465
              Get rid of what?

07:14.467 --> 07:15.934
     Uh, the Republic, sir.

07:15.936 --> 07:18.536
You've been thinking of changing
  the Republic into an empire?

07:18.538 --> 07:19.971
 Who gave you that information?

07:19.973 --> 07:21.539
Well, that's not important, sir.

07:21.541 --> 07:24.041
The important thing is that...
you shouldn't do it.

07:24.043 --> 07:25.376
 Don't listen
 to Pichegru.

07:25.378 --> 07:28.012
If-- If you try to conquer
Europe, you're going to fail.

07:28.014 --> 07:30.015
       What else do you know
          about my plans?

07:30.017 --> 07:31.482
         Uh, well, uh--

07:31.484 --> 07:33.285
Oh, these are
your brothers, aren't they?

07:33.287 --> 07:34.686
[CLEARS THROAT]

07:34.688 --> 07:38.155
   Ah. Oh, yes, you're going to
    turn the Batavian republic

07:38.157 --> 07:40.058
   into the kingdom of Holland,

07:40.060 --> 07:42.093
    and you're gonna give it
     to your brother Louis.

07:43.663 --> 07:46.197
And, uh...
             That's an excellent
                    idea.

07:46.199 --> 07:48.500
You're gonna turn
Hanover and Prussia, um...

07:48.502 --> 07:50.134
over to your brother, Jerome,

07:50.136 --> 07:51.836
  and call it--
  What was--

07:51.838 --> 07:52.871
  Westphalia.

07:52.873 --> 07:54.438
                  Westphalia.

07:54.440 --> 07:55.740
And Joseph is going to get

07:55.742 --> 07:57.408
the Bourbon throne
of the two Sicilys.

07:57.410 --> 07:58.410
                   Why not?

07:58.412 --> 07:59.577
        You're a genius.

08:01.148 --> 08:03.214
     What I really want to
   warn you about is Russia.

08:03.216 --> 08:04.416
         What about Russia?

08:04.418 --> 08:06.284
  Well, the Russian campaign's
           a mistake.

08:06.286 --> 08:07.685
      What Russian campaign?

08:07.687 --> 08:09.120
   You're going to attack it.

08:09.122 --> 08:10.422
                Attack Russia?
                 Are you mad?

08:10.424 --> 08:12.190
Now, you mustn't
go through with it, sir.

08:12.192 --> 08:14.092
If you attack Russia,
you're gonna suffer

08:14.094 --> 08:15.660
one of the worst defeats
in history.

08:15.662 --> 08:17.328
             Napoleon, defeated?
 Yes.

08:21.834 --> 08:23.468
       I'm coming to that.

08:23.470 --> 08:24.936
      You're coming to what?

08:28.741 --> 08:29.975
     Oh, uh-- Uh, Waterloo.

08:29.977 --> 08:31.376
Don't fight
Wellington there.

08:31.378 --> 08:32.376
If you do, you'll--

08:32.379 --> 08:34.145
You'll end up
being sent to Elba.

08:34.147 --> 08:35.746
         Never mind Elba.

08:35.748 --> 08:37.982
           So you think it will
               be a mistake

08:37.984 --> 08:40.018
          for me to turn Europe
             into an empire?

08:40.020 --> 08:42.086
A disaster.

08:42.087 --> 08:43.721
                    I must think
                     about this.

08:43.722 --> 08:45.957
Well, you'll never regret
talking to me, sir.

08:45.959 --> 08:48.259
       We will talk again later.
            Join the others.

08:48.261 --> 08:49.727
               There's plenty of
                food and drink.

08:49.729 --> 08:51.963
Yes, yes. Oh, I've, uh,
been meaning to

08:51.965 --> 08:53.097
ask you about, uh--

08:53.099 --> 08:55.533
           These wool uniforms.

08:58.271 --> 09:00.838
Tell General Pichegru
I want him immediately.

09:05.812 --> 09:07.812
            Attack Russia.

09:07.814 --> 09:09.447
       It would be an insanity.

09:09.449 --> 09:11.015
                 The man is mad.

09:11.017 --> 09:12.751
       Mad or a spy.

09:12.753 --> 09:14.119
                But who would've
                    sent him?

09:14.121 --> 09:15.386
    Russia, of course.

09:17.257 --> 09:18.990
  I've been thinking
      of Russia.

09:21.028 --> 09:24.663
The hungry iceberg waiting
to destroy an unwary army.

09:24.665 --> 09:26.531
  And suddenly this clumsy spy
          comes to me

09:26.533 --> 09:27.899
     and tells me
   not to attack it.

09:27.901 --> 09:30.568
       Oh, why would Russia send
      him here to tell you that?

09:30.570 --> 09:33.805
   For only one reason,
    my dear Pichegru.

09:33.807 --> 09:35.040
      It could be
    that the iceberg

09:35.042 --> 09:36.975
   is not as terrifying
       as it seems.

09:38.311 --> 09:40.645
     Russia must have
    something to fear.

09:40.647 --> 09:43.148
And it could only have something
  to fear if it's vulnerable.

09:44.818 --> 09:46.051
            We will attack!

09:47.788 --> 09:49.387
       And it shall be
     my greatest victory.

09:50.891 --> 09:52.557
                    As you wish,
                        sire.

09:52.559 --> 09:54.826
            And what shall we do
               with this spy?

10:06.339 --> 10:07.438
                  [BLOWS]

10:09.009 --> 10:11.376
It certainly is a pleasure
meeting you, madam.

10:11.378 --> 10:12.710
                 Of course.

10:12.712 --> 10:14.145
I've read a great
deal about you,

10:14.147 --> 10:15.313
but I must say,

10:15.315 --> 10:17.415
you're much more beautiful
than your paintings.

10:17.417 --> 10:18.416
                  Am I?
       Yes.

10:18.418 --> 10:20.218
 [CHUCKLES]

10:20.220 --> 10:21.218
                       Master?

10:21.220 --> 10:22.253
 [COUGHS]

10:22.255 --> 10:23.855
            May I speak with you
              a moment, please?

10:23.857 --> 10:24.889
            "Master"?

10:24.891 --> 10:26.958
Yes. Yeah, it's a pet name.
                Ah.

10:26.960 --> 10:28.225
Would you
excuse me, please?

10:28.227 --> 10:29.226
[CLEARS THROAT]

10:29.228 --> 10:30.662
    Pardon me.

10:30.664 --> 10:32.030
                  Jeannie, um...

10:32.032 --> 10:33.031
                    I'm busy.

10:33.033 --> 10:34.766
      Mm. So I see.

10:34.768 --> 10:35.967
                  Ye-- What do
                   you want?

10:35.969 --> 10:38.069
Master, you wish to change
the course of history.

10:38.071 --> 10:39.570
                     Yes.
Then I think you have done it.

10:39.572 --> 10:40.838
               What do you mean?

10:40.840 --> 10:43.474
You have just talked Napoleon
into attacking Russia.

10:43.476 --> 10:45.609
He thinks you're a spy,
and he's going to kill you.

10:45.611 --> 10:47.578
        No, no, no. I'm sure you
           misunderstood him.

10:47.580 --> 10:49.280
       Yes, he is.
     I had a long talk with him.

10:49.282 --> 10:50.948
         He was very amenable
           to everythi--

10:50.950 --> 10:52.416
          We-- Now, fellas.
           Wait a minute.

10:52.418 --> 10:53.417
          Wait. Napoleon.

10:53.419 --> 10:54.618
                    [MAN SPEAKS
                   INDISTINCTLY]

10:54.620 --> 10:56.087
            You are new?

10:56.089 --> 10:57.955
Oh, no, no, no.
I am old.

10:57.957 --> 10:59.290
          I mean, you are new
              at my court?

10:59.292 --> 11:00.491
   Oh, yes, sir.

11:00.493 --> 11:02.660
  But, of course, it is
  a very old court. Ha.

11:02.662 --> 11:03.828
                    You are very
                     beautiful.

11:03.830 --> 11:05.296
                  Oh, thank you.

11:05.298 --> 11:07.231
 What is your name,
     my child?

11:07.233 --> 11:08.232
               Oh-- Uh, Jeannie.

11:08.234 --> 11:09.433
    Jeannie?
                   Uh-huh.

11:09.435 --> 11:11.535
Well, Jeannie. I would like
to see and talk to you,

11:11.537 --> 11:12.737
and get to
know you better.

11:12.739 --> 11:14.872
And perhaps, we could
meet later tonight?

11:14.874 --> 11:16.674
         Oh. I am afraid not.

11:16.676 --> 11:19.410
      Uh-- A friend of mine
     is in <i> terrible</i> trouble.

11:19.412 --> 11:21.078
 I could get your friend
     out of trouble.

11:21.080 --> 11:23.514
              Oh. No, thank you.

11:23.516 --> 11:26.717
   But you are going to be much
 too busy worrying about Russia.

11:40.267 --> 11:41.766
            [GASPS]
       Hey, I'm a major.

11:41.768 --> 11:43.668
      You guys can't go around
        hitting an officer.

11:43.670 --> 11:44.669
           What's the matter--

11:44.671 --> 11:46.538
                 Go in the cell.
      Get in there.

11:48.508 --> 11:50.141
                     What time
                   is this, uh--

11:50.143 --> 11:51.543
                  [MAKES CUTTING
                      SOUND]

11:51.545 --> 11:52.877
    Dawn.

12:04.390 --> 12:06.257
             Sorry, madam.
             No visitors.
       Oh.

12:11.631 --> 12:12.897
                        Wha--?

12:31.251 --> 12:32.483
I'm sorry
I am late, master,

12:32.485 --> 12:33.985
 but your friend Napoleon
        Bonaparte

12:33.987 --> 12:35.386
wanted to talk with me.

12:35.388 --> 12:37.021
                    Yes?
He asked me to return later.

12:37.023 --> 12:38.222
      [GIGGLES]

12:38.224 --> 12:39.757
Well, are you ready
to go home now?

12:39.759 --> 12:41.359
              Yeah, we can't
                 go now.

12:41.361 --> 12:43.527
   Oh, of course
   we can, master.

12:43.529 --> 12:45.529
      No, no. I mean we can't go
          and leave Napoleon

12:45.531 --> 12:47.332
               in the lurch
                like this.

12:47.334 --> 12:48.732
  Oh, but he thinks
    you're a spy.

12:48.734 --> 12:50.068
He will not listen to you.

12:50.070 --> 12:52.136
             Yeah. That's right.

12:52.138 --> 12:53.438
                 Jeannie.
       Hm?

12:53.440 --> 12:55.206
        You can make him listen.
        I?

12:55.208 --> 12:57.342
      Yes, yes. Didn't you say
      he wanted you to return?

12:57.344 --> 12:58.509
            Yes.

12:58.511 --> 13:00.478
 Did he seem interested in you?

13:00.480 --> 13:02.981
            Well...

13:02.983 --> 13:04.115
              yes.

13:04.117 --> 13:05.516
    But you are the only man
            that I--

13:05.518 --> 13:06.784
 I want you to go to his palace.

13:06.786 --> 13:08.285
        Oh, but why?

13:08.287 --> 13:10.954
 Because you've got to convince
  him that if he starts a war,

13:10.956 --> 13:12.423
        it's gonna lead
       to a catastrophe.

13:12.425 --> 13:13.691
Now, you think you can do that?

13:13.693 --> 13:17.195
 Oh. But I do not know anything
       about war, master.

13:17.197 --> 13:18.196
           [CHUCKLES]

13:18.198 --> 13:19.763
     But you know something
           about men.

13:19.765 --> 13:20.998
        [GIGGLES]

13:21.000 --> 13:22.100
           I do.

13:22.102 --> 13:23.835
                    I want you
                 to flatter him.

13:23.837 --> 13:25.837
             He has a tremendous
                     ego.

13:25.839 --> 13:28.840
Uh, you've got to make him think
  that all of this is his idea.

13:28.842 --> 13:30.074
                 Jeannie...

13:30.076 --> 13:32.544
          this is a tremendously
            important mission.

13:32.546 --> 13:34.579
  Oh, master.

13:34.581 --> 13:36.147
      Are you choosing me
        for this mission

13:36.149 --> 13:37.715
   because I am the only one
          in the world

13:37.717 --> 13:39.250
        who can do it?

13:39.252 --> 13:40.718
        I'm choosing you
        for this mission

13:40.720 --> 13:42.554
        because there's
       nobody else here.

13:42.556 --> 13:44.556
  Now, pop over to the palace
     and go to work on him.

13:44.558 --> 13:46.390
       Go to work on him.
          Yes, master.

13:46.392 --> 13:47.391
     And do not worry.

13:47.393 --> 13:49.360
 I will handle it <i> brilliantly.</i>

13:49.362 --> 13:51.195
    And remember, be subtle.

13:51.197 --> 13:52.563
        He's got to think
         it's his idea.

13:52.565 --> 13:55.766
Oh, I am probably the most
subtle genie in the whole world.

13:55.768 --> 13:56.834
        [BOTH CHUCKLING]

13:58.805 --> 14:00.138
      Oh. That's my girl.

14:00.140 --> 14:01.338
           Oh.

14:02.909 --> 14:04.008
              What does "subtle"
                     mean?

14:04.010 --> 14:05.243
          Go!

14:09.549 --> 14:12.850
Our troops will
march in through here,

14:12.852 --> 14:15.053
toward the soft
underbelly of Europe,

14:15.055 --> 14:16.520
and into the Caucasus.

14:16.522 --> 14:17.688
                 No, Pichegru.

14:17.690 --> 14:18.756
                 I have changed
                    my mind.

14:18.758 --> 14:19.923
           But why?

14:19.925 --> 14:22.660
        Russia sits on Europe
          like a sleepy bear,

14:22.662 --> 14:25.162
      ready to devour anything
        that comes near it.

14:25.164 --> 14:26.898
     Only a fool would attack.

14:26.900 --> 14:29.600
       Then what do we do
        about this, uh,

14:29.602 --> 14:31.402
     Major Nelson, the spy?

14:31.404 --> 14:33.704
        We have no proof
   that he was sent by Russia.

14:35.141 --> 14:36.274
                      I am back.

14:36.276 --> 14:38.476
       Oh, what a pleasant
            surprise.
                          Ha-ha.

14:38.478 --> 14:40.878
           You have met
         General Pichegru?

14:40.880 --> 14:42.380
       This is Mademoiselle
             Jeannie.

14:42.382 --> 14:44.181
             Oh. You are the one
                 who is going

14:44.183 --> 14:45.483
                  to try to kill
                     Napoleon,

14:45.485 --> 14:47.451
              and he is going to
             have you strangled.

14:47.453 --> 14:49.620
 But she's outrageous, sire.

14:49.622 --> 14:51.389
But so beautiful.

14:51.391 --> 14:52.823
                     Oh.
                  [GIGGLES]

14:52.825 --> 14:55.326
Pichegru, would you
     excuse us?

14:55.328 --> 14:57.161
        You, uh--

14:57.163 --> 14:59.664
    You would not, uh,
    change your mind?

14:59.666 --> 15:01.699
No, call all
the plans off.

15:01.701 --> 15:03.367
As you command,
sire.

15:05.905 --> 15:07.271
    I thought you were
       not coming.

15:07.273 --> 15:08.840
 You said you had
 to help a friend.

15:08.842 --> 15:10.341
                  Oh, but I am
                  helping him.

15:10.343 --> 15:12.010
          That is why I am here.

15:12.012 --> 15:13.244
But I don't
understand.

15:13.246 --> 15:15.446
          Oh, Major Nelson
    sent me here to work on you.

15:15.448 --> 15:16.480
To work on me?

15:16.482 --> 15:17.514
                       Yes.

15:17.516 --> 15:20.151
             But he said that
             I must be subtle.

15:20.153 --> 15:21.853
              What does "subtle"
                     mean?

15:21.855 --> 15:23.254
It means honest.

15:23.256 --> 15:25.823
It means that you must tell me
everything Major Nelson said.

15:25.825 --> 15:27.225
                     Oh.

15:27.227 --> 15:29.927
             Well, he said that
           it was very important

15:29.929 --> 15:32.229
         that I try to talk you
        out of attacking Russia,

15:32.231 --> 15:34.832
        but that you must think
       that it is your own idea,

15:34.834 --> 15:36.768
                because you have
               a tremendous ego.

15:37.870 --> 15:39.203
          Is that subtle enough?

15:39.205 --> 15:40.971
Indeed it is.

15:40.973 --> 15:43.707
                 Oh, I knew
               I could do it.

15:43.709 --> 15:46.010
   So he's trying to
    trick Napoleon

15:46.012 --> 15:48.112
  into not declaring war.

15:49.648 --> 15:51.682
Any fool can see that
the bear is sleeping.

15:51.684 --> 15:53.217
                Oh.

15:53.219 --> 15:56.154
 Waiting to fall into the hands
      of an invading army.

15:56.156 --> 15:58.155
     Nothing shall stop me.
      Thank you, my dear.

15:58.157 --> 15:59.890
        Oh, you are welcome.

15:59.892 --> 16:01.526
         What did I do?

16:02.761 --> 16:06.063
You have reminded me
of France's glorious destiny.

16:06.065 --> 16:07.431
          [RINGS BELL]

16:09.102 --> 16:12.536
Nothing shall stop France
from ruling the world.

16:12.538 --> 16:13.537
                    Oh.

16:13.539 --> 16:14.738
Arrest this woman.

16:14.740 --> 16:16.440
             Oh, am I going to
               the Bastille?

16:16.442 --> 16:17.441
I'm afraid so.

16:17.443 --> 16:18.976
             Oh, thank you.
                Mwah.

16:18.978 --> 16:20.211
                       [LAUGHS]
                     Come along.

16:34.327 --> 16:37.694
 <i> ["LA MARSEILLAISE" PLAYING]</i>

16:39.798 --> 16:40.831
        [KEYS JINGLING]

16:42.101 --> 16:43.200
         [GIGGLES]
       Ah, thank you.

16:44.337 --> 16:45.936
               Thank heavens
           you're back, Jeannie.

16:45.938 --> 16:47.505
                I knew you could
                     do it.
[DOOR LOCKS]

16:47.507 --> 16:50.341
              I said to myself--
               What went wrong?

16:50.343 --> 16:52.709
   Nothing, master.
  I was very subtle.

16:52.711 --> 16:54.111
 I told him everything.

16:54.113 --> 16:55.513
              You-- You told him
                  everything?

16:55.515 --> 16:56.680
    It is all fixed.

16:56.682 --> 16:58.015
                It's all fixed.

16:58.017 --> 17:00.351
Napoleon has decided
not to attack Russia.

17:00.353 --> 17:02.019
                Ha. Good girl.

17:02.021 --> 17:04.155
He is going to attack
a big bear instead.

17:04.156 --> 17:06.557
                  [CHUCKLES]

17:06.559 --> 17:07.858
                     Oh. Oh.

17:07.859 --> 17:10.661
                 You're kidding.
May we go home now, master?

17:10.663 --> 17:12.363
                  No. What am I
                    gonna do?

17:12.365 --> 17:13.364
                    [SNAPS]

17:13.366 --> 17:14.632
                 Wait a minute,
                 wait a minute.

17:14.634 --> 17:16.166
                  I got one last
                      chance.

17:16.169 --> 17:17.468
              I've got to get to
                  Josephine.

17:17.470 --> 17:18.469
Oh, believe me, master,

17:18.471 --> 17:20.137
she's much too old
     for you.

17:21.574 --> 17:23.641
           She's the only one
        Napoleon will listen to.

17:23.643 --> 17:26.143
Now, if I can just talk to her,
yeah, I'm sure she'll help.

17:26.145 --> 17:27.310
                   Oh, master,

17:27.313 --> 17:29.913
    would it not be much simpler
        if we just went home?

17:29.915 --> 17:31.715
      No, we can't
  leave him like this.

17:31.717 --> 17:33.050
Can you get Josephine here?

17:33.052 --> 17:34.585
                 Well, if that
               is what you wish.

17:34.587 --> 17:35.952
That is what I wish.

17:35.954 --> 17:37.020
                   [SIGHS]

17:38.424 --> 17:39.457
         Thank you.

17:39.459 --> 17:40.525
           Uh, now--

17:46.765 --> 17:48.365
                           Oh.

17:48.367 --> 17:49.600
             You have
           five minutes.

17:50.736 --> 17:52.536
I received a message
that you wish to see me

17:52.538 --> 17:53.670
   about my husband.

17:53.672 --> 17:55.439
   The messenger said
  it was life and death.

17:55.441 --> 17:57.741
            Yes. He's absolutely
                   right.

17:57.743 --> 18:00.244
   Uh-- Your husband is about to
      make a terrible mistake.

18:00.246 --> 18:02.546
     Now, you've got to stop him
        from attacking Russia.

18:02.548 --> 18:05.182
Oh, I do not mix in His
Majesty's military affairs.

18:05.184 --> 18:06.850
     Well, if you don't use
        your influence,

18:06.852 --> 18:08.752
     he's gonna wind up on Elba.
         Elba?

18:08.754 --> 18:10.854
       That's the island
 where they're gonna exile him.

18:10.856 --> 18:12.290
        You are joking.

18:12.292 --> 18:13.591
  Of course, you won't be there.

18:13.593 --> 18:14.792
     He'll be married to Louise,

18:14.794 --> 18:16.327
                   but still I--
         Louise?

18:16.329 --> 18:18.862
He's going to escape from Elba,
         raise an army,

18:18.864 --> 18:20.397
       and fight Wellington
           at Waterloo.

18:20.399 --> 18:21.898
         And believe me,
       he's going to lose.

18:21.900 --> 18:23.801
    Who is this "Louise"?

18:23.803 --> 18:25.169
    Well, that's not important.

18:25.171 --> 18:27.571
     The important thing is
you've got to convince Napoleon

18:27.573 --> 18:28.572
     not to go into battle.

18:28.574 --> 18:30.741
   How long has he known her?

18:30.743 --> 18:32.844
              Who?
       Louise!

18:32.846 --> 18:34.312
             Gosh, I don't know.

18:34.314 --> 18:35.779
                Will you talk to
                    Napoleon?

18:35.781 --> 18:37.348
         No.

18:37.350 --> 18:39.550
           N-- No? But you're
        the only chance I have--

18:39.552 --> 18:40.584
             Don't you love him?

18:42.856 --> 18:45.756
I love him more
than life itself.

18:45.758 --> 18:48.592
But how do I know that anything
you're saying is true.

18:48.594 --> 18:50.962
Can you prove that they are
going to exile him to Elba?

18:50.964 --> 18:52.964
               Well, no, I can't
                 prove it. I--

18:52.966 --> 18:56.968
Uh, perhaps if you can tell me
who this Louise is,

18:56.970 --> 18:59.237
I could find out
whether you are lying,

18:59.239 --> 19:01.906
or whether you really know
what's going to happen.

19:01.908 --> 19:03.074
                 You-- You mean,
                    if I could

19:03.076 --> 19:04.942
                show her to you,
               you'd believe me?

19:04.944 --> 19:06.410
      Perhaps.

19:06.412 --> 19:08.479
       Her name is Marie Louise,
         and she's the daughter

19:08.481 --> 19:10.614
                of the empress
                 of Austria.

19:10.616 --> 19:13.084
He has never
mentioned her to me.

19:13.086 --> 19:15.086
  Do you think you can find her?
[KEYS JINGLING]

19:15.088 --> 19:16.954
     Don't worry.
    I'll find <i> her.</i>

19:16.956 --> 19:18.189
                 Yeah. Thank you
                    very much.

19:18.191 --> 19:19.757
             Uh-- You don't have
              a moment to lose.

19:19.759 --> 19:21.225
          Have you finished,
            Your Majesty?

19:21.227 --> 19:22.894
Yes. For now.

19:31.804 --> 19:32.803
                   Master.
      Oh.

19:32.805 --> 19:33.804
               How did it go?

19:33.806 --> 19:35.138
    Oh, just fine.

19:35.140 --> 19:37.641
I think I finally found
a way to persuade Josephine

19:37.643 --> 19:38.976
that I'm telling the truth.

19:38.978 --> 19:40.444
We can help Napoleon now.

19:40.446 --> 19:42.546
                Do you know what
                I think, master?
        What?

19:42.548 --> 19:45.015
   That I should have let you
go to your lecture this morning.

19:45.017 --> 19:46.350
       Yeah.

19:47.486 --> 19:48.685
            [KEYS JINGLING]

19:51.090 --> 19:52.089
                     Ah. Did you
                      find her?

19:52.091 --> 19:53.524
   Oh,<i> mais oui,</i> monsieur.

19:53.526 --> 19:56.327
But first, I want to be very
sure of what you have told me.

19:56.329 --> 19:58.129
This Marie Louise
of Austria

19:58.131 --> 19:59.931
and my husband are in love,

19:59.933 --> 20:01.332
and are going to be married?

20:01.334 --> 20:03.401
             Oh, yes. Oh, yes.
          They're madly in love.

20:03.403 --> 20:04.668
       [CHUCKLES]

20:04.670 --> 20:06.304
      Bring her in.

20:08.441 --> 20:10.007
[BABY GIGGLES]

20:10.009 --> 20:12.176
                       Ah. Ah-
                    ha-ha-ha-ha.

20:12.178 --> 20:13.411
                 Hi there, huh?

20:13.413 --> 20:15.012
             [MAKES BABY NOISES]

20:15.014 --> 20:16.413
                   Who-- Who's
                   this? She--

20:16.415 --> 20:19.883
       This is the princess
     Marie Louise of Austria.

20:22.188 --> 20:23.253
         Take her away.

20:25.958 --> 20:27.391
Happy guillotine,
monsieur.

20:28.360 --> 20:30.327
            Hey. Wait. Uh,
            wait a minute--

20:30.329 --> 20:31.528
           Uh-- I-I-I made
              a mistake.

20:31.530 --> 20:32.963
         I-I got the dates
             mixed up.

20:32.965 --> 20:34.832
   If you just wait 18 years,
         I assure you,

20:34.834 --> 20:36.000
   they're gonna be married.

20:36.002 --> 20:37.034
            Happily.

20:38.204 --> 20:39.269
         Ah!
                  Master.

20:39.271 --> 20:40.771
     [SIGHS]
       When I was at the palace,

20:40.773 --> 20:43.140
        I saw the most beautiful
                dresses.

20:43.142 --> 20:44.775
             Oh, I would love to
              have a new dress.

20:44.777 --> 20:46.343
Is that all you
think of, is dresses?

20:46.345 --> 20:47.845
             You never take me
             to Paris, master.

20:47.847 --> 20:49.814
         And while we are here,
       let me get one new dress.

20:49.816 --> 20:51.415
Yeah, would you forget
the dresses--

20:51.417 --> 20:53.317
I will be back in a few minutes.
   Yeah, but--

20:54.720 --> 20:56.253
       Jeannie, you can't
         leave me now.

20:56.255 --> 20:57.988
    They're gonna come for me
          any minute.

20:57.990 --> 20:59.990
        I'm not kidding.
 They're gonna cut my head off.

20:59.992 --> 21:00.991
       Now, come on back.

21:00.993 --> 21:02.426
[FOOTSTEPS]

21:26.486 --> 21:28.552
          "Major Anthony Nelson,

21:28.554 --> 21:30.654
             "by the order of
         the Emperor of France--

21:30.656 --> 21:32.022
  You're bringing a pardon.

21:32.024 --> 21:33.156
                      Right.

21:33.158 --> 21:35.259
[LAUGHS]

21:35.961 --> 21:36.960
          I knew it.

21:36.962 --> 21:38.695
                   But...
       Yes, yes?

21:38.697 --> 21:41.998
           first you are being
              guillotined!

21:42.000 --> 21:43.567
            Now, let's go!

21:43.569 --> 21:45.469
I just want you to know
about killing majors.

21:45.471 --> 21:46.636
         I happen to be
          an American.

21:46.638 --> 21:47.904
     [INDISTINCT SHOUTING]

21:47.906 --> 21:49.005
       Wait a minute! Wait!

21:52.344 --> 21:53.343
                        GUARD:
                     Move! Move!

21:53.345 --> 21:54.778
  Hey, just
  a minute.

21:54.780 --> 21:56.713
Listen, I want to
see a lawyer.

22:00.185 --> 22:02.052
            Come on,
            monsieur.

22:02.054 --> 22:03.053
          Up, up, up.

22:03.055 --> 22:05.355
        Where do you
        think you are?

22:05.357 --> 22:07.390
      Believe me,
       monsieur.

22:07.392 --> 22:09.292
It will be over
in less than a minute.

22:09.294 --> 22:11.494
              I'm not interested
              in your timetable.

22:11.496 --> 22:13.063
               I demand to see
             Napoleon Bonaparte.

22:13.065 --> 22:16.232
You are really not in a position
to demand anything, are you?

22:16.234 --> 22:17.935
Take him,
executioner.

22:17.937 --> 22:18.935
           Oh!
Come on!

22:18.937 --> 22:20.437
We would like to
see you die.

22:20.439 --> 22:22.106
                 [TONY SHOUTING]

22:23.209 --> 22:25.309
          Hey. Hey, you.
            Come here.

22:25.311 --> 22:27.310
            Listen, you're
       making a mistake, fella.

22:27.312 --> 22:28.912
        I'm on detached duty
              to NASA.

22:28.914 --> 22:30.280
Go on! Down!
              [GRUNTS]

22:31.250 --> 22:34.684
Monsieur. Do you
have any last words?

22:34.686 --> 22:36.386
           Just one.

22:36.388 --> 22:38.021
            Jeannie!

22:38.758 --> 22:40.524
          [WHIMPERING]

22:40.526 --> 22:41.759
           Jeannie--!

22:41.761 --> 22:42.760
            Jeannie!

22:42.762 --> 22:44.128
             Yeah--
           [GRUNTING]

22:49.434 --> 22:51.268
             Jeannie! Get me
              out of here.

22:51.270 --> 22:52.470
         Jeannie, where are you?

22:52.472 --> 22:53.804
Here it is, master.

22:53.806 --> 22:55.172
Is it not beautiful?

22:55.174 --> 22:56.774
              Oh, yes, it's just
                   gorgeous.

22:56.776 --> 22:59.109
      Now, would you mind taking
      this thing off of me. Huh?

22:59.111 --> 23:00.177
    Hm?

23:00.179 --> 23:01.445
       Oh.
                   Yes.

23:02.615 --> 23:03.614
     [SIGHS]

23:03.616 --> 23:05.716
               Oh, thank you.
            Thank you very much.

23:05.718 --> 23:07.618
              Uh-- Oh, would you
                  mind? Here.

23:07.620 --> 23:08.852
          The ropes too, huh?
  Hm?

23:08.854 --> 23:09.853
      Oh.

23:11.957 --> 23:13.957
               Oh. Thank you.
            Thank you very much.

23:13.959 --> 23:16.560
            J-Jeannie, can't you
             do anything right?

23:16.562 --> 23:18.762
Oh, I am sorry,
master, but...

23:18.764 --> 23:21.031
after all, I am only human.

23:29.074 --> 23:30.508
           What are you writing,
                  master?

23:30.510 --> 23:32.442
Oh, just a minute.

23:32.444 --> 23:33.511
There. Read it.

23:34.513 --> 23:37.815
            JEANNIE:
  "Able was I ere I saw Elba."

23:37.817 --> 23:38.849
    Mm-hm.

23:38.851 --> 23:40.851
            Huh. Well, what does
                  it mean?

23:40.853 --> 23:42.519
Oh. Well, when you
spell it backwards,

23:42.521 --> 23:44.554
it comes out
exactly the same.

23:44.556 --> 23:48.158
            "Able was I, E, R--"

23:48.160 --> 23:50.493
              Eh-- Oh, "I saw"--

23:50.495 --> 23:51.729
                    [LAUGHS]
                  Oh. it does.

23:51.731 --> 23:52.730
     Yes.

23:52.732 --> 23:54.531
                   Oh, you're
               a genius, master.

23:54.533 --> 23:55.766
   Oh, no.

23:55.768 --> 23:57.901
You know, I'm glad we took
that trip before I gave

23:57.903 --> 23:59.203
that lecture on Napoleon.

